{{Orphan|date=May 2015}}
{{Expand German|topic=culture|date=April 2010|Ambrosius Eßer}} '''Ambrosius Eßer''' [[Dominican Order|OP]] (born '''Klaus Eßer''', also spelled '''Eszer''', or '''Esser''', 19 November 1933, [[Düsseldorf]] – 12 April 2010, [[Berlin]]) was a [[Germany|German]] church historian and member of the [[Dominican Order]]. He died of a [[pulmonary embolism]].
Eszer served for many years as professor at the [[Pontifical University of Saint Thomas Aquinas|Pontifical University of St. Thomas Aquinas, ''Angelicum'']] in Rome, Italy.
