{{nihongo|'''Chōryaku'''|長暦}} was a {{nihongo|[[Japanese era name|Japanese era]]|年号,|''nengō'',|lit. "year name"}} after ''[[Chōgen]]'' and before ''[[Chōkyū]].''  This period spanned the years from April 1037<ref>Nussbaum, Louis-Frédéric. (2005). "''Chōgen''" in {{Google books|p2QnPijAEmEC|''Japan Encyclopedia'', p. 118|page=118}}; n.b., Louis-Frédéric is pseudonym of Louis-Frédéric Nussbaum, ''see'' [https://archive.is/20120524174828/http://dispatch.opac.ddb.de/DB=4.1/PPN?PPN=128842709 Deutsche Nationalbibliothek Authority File].</ref> through 1040.<ref>Nussbaum, "''Chōkyū''" at {{Google books|p2QnPijAEmEC|p. 121.|page=121}}</ref> The reigning emperor was {{nihongo|[[Emperor Go-Suzaku of Japan|Go-Suzaku]]''-tennō''|後朱雀天皇}}.<ref>Titsingh, Isaac. (1834). ''Annales des empereurs du Japon'', pp. 160-162; Brown, Delmer ''et al.'' (1979). {{Google books|w4f5FrmIJKIC|''Gukanshō'', pp. 310-311|page=310}}; Varley, H. Paul. (1980). ''Jinnō Shōtōki.'' p. 195-196.</ref>

==Change of era==
* '''1037''' {{nihongo|''Chōryaku gannen''|長暦元年|}}: The new era name was created to mark an event or series of events. The previous era ended and the new one commenced in ''Chōgen'' 10, on the 21st day of the 4th month of 1037.<ref name="brown311">Brown, p. 311.</ref>

==Events of the ''Chōryaku'' era==
* '''1037''' (''Chōryaku 1, 2nd day of the 7th month''): The eldest son of Emperor Go-Suzaku (Prince Chikihito, who was would become Emperor Go-Reizei) has his coming of age ceremony.<ref name="brown311"/> 
* '''1037''' (''Chōryaku 1, 17th day of the 8th month''): Go-Suzaku formally names Chikihito as his heir and Crown Prince.<ref name="brown311"/>
* '''1038''' (''Chōryaku 2, 1st day of the 9th month''): Fujiwara no Chikaie was killed by a servant during an  attempted robbery; and all the greats of the Fujiwara went into mourning.<ref>''Monumenta Nipponica,'' Vol. 59, p. 399.</ref>

