'''Krasimir Donchev Karakachanov''' ({{lang-bg|Красимир Дончев Каракачанов}}; born 29 March 1965) is a  Bulgarian politician, PhD in international law and international relations and historian. He is currently the leader of the [[IMRO – Bulgarian National Movement]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.webcafe.bg/id_1490585911_Dedovite_chervenotikvenicheta |title=Дедовите червенотиквеничета|accessdate=31 March 2014 |date=10 February 2014 |language=Bulgarian |website=webcafe.bg}}</ref> and [[Ministry of Defence (Bulgaria)|Minister of Defence]].<ref>http://www.mod.bg/en/ministry_minister.html</ref>

== Biography ==
Krasimir Karakachanov claims that he does not have any roots from the [[Macedonia (region)|Macedonian]] region, but as a historian he became a specialist on the issue.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vestnikataka.com/?module=displaystory&story_id=17856&format=print&edition_id=258|title=Красимир Каракачанов, депутат, лидер на ВМРО: Кандидатурата на Беронов е с предизвестен крах}}</ref>
Karakachanov was a candidate in the 2016 and [[Bulgarian presidential election, 2011|2011 presidential election]], winning 15% and 1% of all votes cast and placed 3rd and 10th respectively.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://results.cik.bg/tur1/prezidentski/index.html|title=Гласове за избиране на президент и вицепрезидент|accessdate=31 March 2014|date=2011|language=Bulgarian|publisher=cik.bg|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331231124/http://results.cik.bg/tur1/prezidentski/index.html|archivedate=31 March 2014|df=}}</ref> Karakachanov took part in the [[European Parliament election, 2014 (Bulgaria)|2014 European elections]] as part of a coalition bloc with the [[Bulgaria without Censorship]] political party.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.standartnews.com/balgariya-politika/_balgariya_bez_tsenzura_vmro_i_zns_veche_ofitsialno_sa_koalitsiya-230019.html |title=България без цензура", ВМРО и ЗНС вече официално са коалиция|accessdate=17 May 2014 |date=16 March 2014 |language=Bulgarian |publisher=standartnews.com}}</ref> In late July 2014, Karakachanov's IMRO left the coalition to form a [[Patriotic Front (Bulgaria)|Patriotic Front]] [[electoral alliance]] together with [[Valeri Simeonov]]'s [[National Front for the Salvation of Bulgaria]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mediapool.bg/vmro-reshi-da-napusne-barekov-zaradi-sayuz-s-nfsb-news223012.html|title=ВМРО реши да напусне Бареков заради съюз с НФСБ|accessdate=12 August 2014 |date=24 July 2014 |language=Bulgarian |publisher=mediapool.bg}}</ref> With Simeonov, he is the co-spokesman for the electoral bloc.

Before 1989, during the communist era, Karakachanov, being a historian, was an informer of the [[Committee for State Security]] on [[Macedonian nationalism]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.robert-schuman.eu/en/eem/1161-the-candidate-of-the-ruling-party-rossen-plevneliev-running-favourite-in-the-presidential-election-in-bulgaria-just-one-week-before-the-vote |title=The candidate of the ruling party, Rossen Plevneliev, running favourite in the presidential election in Bulgaria just one week before the vote |work=The European Elections Monitor |publisher=Fondation Robert Schuman |date=17 October 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://sofiaecho.com/2011/09/27/1163815_four-of-bulgarias-presidential-candidates-were-communist-era-state-security-collaborators |title=Four of Bulgaria's presidential candidates were communist-era State Security collaborators |newspaper=The Sofia Echo |date=27 September 2011}}</ref>

Karakachanov stood as the candidate of the [[United Patriots]] coalition in the [[Bulgarian presidential election, 2016|2016 presidential election]], with the MP [[Yavor Notev]] of [[Attack (political party)|Attack]] as his vice presidential candidate.
They finished in third place with 573,016 votes or 14.97%.

