{{Infobox museum | name = Salakta Archaeological Museum | native_name = المتحف الأثري بسلقطة. | native_name_lang = | image = Tunisie Musée Salakta.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Musée Salakta | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | coordinates = | established = | location = [[Salakta]], [[Tunisia]] | type = [[museum#Archaeology museums|Archaeology museum]] | collection = ancient [[Sullectum]] art | visitors = | director = | president = | curator = | publictransit = | car_park = | network = | website = }}
The '''Salakta Archaeological Museum''' is a [[Tunisia]]n [[museum#Archaeology museums|archaeological museum]], located in [[Salakta]]. Established in 1980, it includes archaeological works from the ancient [[Sullectum]], especially [[terra cotta]], a [[mosaic]] pavement representing a gigantic [[African lion]], and [[amphorae]] from other sites in the [[Sahel, Tunisia]].
