{{Infobox scientist | name = Sen Arevshatyan | image = Sen S. Arevshatyan.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1928|01|07}} | birth_place = [[Yerevan]], [[Armenian Soviet Socialist Republic]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|2014|07|25|1928|01|07}} | death_place = [[Yerevan]], [[Republic of Armenia]] | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | residence = | citizenship = [[Armenia]] | nationality = [[Armenians|Armenian]] | fields = History }} '''Sen S. Arevshatyan''' ({{lang-hy|Սեն Սուրենի Արևշատյան}}, 7 January 1928 &ndash; 25 July 2014)<ref>{{cite news|title=Renowned scholar Sen Arevshatyan dies|url=http://www.tert.am/en/news/2014/07/25/Sen-arevshatyan/1150093|agency=[[Tert.am]]|date=25 July 2014}}</ref> was an [[Armenia]]n scholar, whose works are devoted to the history of ancient and medieval Armenian [[philosophy]] and historical sources. He is also specialized in the publication of critical texts and scientific translations of medieval works.<ref>[http://www.sci.am/membersview.php?l=&id=82&oid=&oid2=&d=&langid=2 Sen S. Arevshatyan, National Academy of Sciences of RA]</ref> His researched focused on the 5th century philosopher [[David the Invincible]].<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Editorial Board|title=Սեն Արևշատյան [Sen Arevshatyan]|journal=[[Patma-Banasirakan Handes]]|date=2014|issue=2|pages=257–258|url=http://hpj.asj-oa.am/5991/|language=hy|issn=0135-0536}}</ref>
Arevshatyan was a member of the Paris-based International Academy “Ararat” since 1993 and the International Academy of Natural and Social Sciences. He was the founder and chairman of the Cultural Found of Armenia (1986–1989) and an Honored Citizen of [[Yerevan]].<ref>[http://armlet1600.sci.am/gitxorh.php?id=3&langid=3 Sen S. Arevshatyan] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070811051955/http://armlet1600.sci.am/gitxorh.php?id=3&langid=3 |date=2007-08-11 }}</ref> Arevshatyan was awarded the State Prize of the [[Armenian SSR]] in 1978. He has been a member of [[Armenian Academy of Sciences]] presidium, ex-director of [[Matenadaran]] for more than two decades.
